#, no-wrap
msgid "Hats Term Limits Policy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rationale"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:11
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Core team appoints several individuals (\"hats\") that perform "
"critical roles within the project. It is important to reduce single points "
"of failure in these roles. Additionally, turnover in hats can provide fresh "
"insight and help avoid burnout."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:13
msgid ""
"The current set of core-appointed hats is core secretary, head release "
"engineer, the security officer, and postmaster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:15
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Core team has approved the following hats term limits "
"policy. This was first posted to the Developers mailing list on June 22, "
"2012, and amended in June 2015."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:19
msgid "An individual may serve as a core-appointed hat given that:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:21
msgid "Core approves their appointment or re-appointment to the role."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:22
msgid "The individual is willing to continue."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:23
msgid "The individual is still able to perform the role effectively."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:25
msgid ""
"Hats are appointed at the pleasure of core. Appointments may be rescinded by "
"core at any time where this serves the needs of the project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:27
msgid ""
"Each hat's term begins three months after the start of a core team's two "
"year term and ends three months after the end of the core team's term. Hats "
"are explicitly approved by the new core team at the start of the hat's term."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:29
msgid ""
"If a hat becomes vacant during a term, core shall appoint a replacement for "
"the remainder of the term."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:31
msgid "Core shall review all hats annually."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:33
msgid ""
"In general it is expected that volunteers serving in hat positions will be "
"limited to serving for four consecutive years, rounded up to the first "
"natural review/appointment cycle."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:35
msgid ""
"Non volunteers serving in hat positions are still expected to participate in "
"annual reviews and provide for continuity to core's satisfaction."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:37
msgid ""
"Each hat must appoint a deputy who can cover their role in the case of "
"absence or illness, and be trained and ready to take over the role (subject "
"to core approval) should the role holder resign before the end of their "
"term."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:39
msgid ""
"If a core team is dissolved prematurely, then the next term for each hat "
"will begin three months after the new core team's term begins."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/hats.adoc:40
msgid ""
"These limits apply to individual hats and not to teams. For teams with a "
"single lead role, the limits shall apply to the lead role. An individual "
"that is not eligible to serve as the lead of a team may continue to serve as "
"a member of the team."
msgstr ""
